{"title_page": "Inter Expo Center \u2013 Tsarigradsko shose Metro Station", "text_new": "{{Short description|S\u043efia metro station}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name                = [[File:Sofia Metro Logo.svg|27px|link=Sofia Metro]] IEC - Tsarigradsko shose\n| style               = Sofia Metro\n| image               = \u0426\u0430\u0440\u0438\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e-\u0432\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0431\u044e\u043b.jpg\n| coordinates         = {{coord|42|38|58.62|N|23|23|37.01|E|display=inline,title}}\n| owned               = [[Sofia#Administration|Sofia Municipality]]\n| platforms           = side\n| levels              = 3\n| tracks              = 2\n| structure           = sub-surface\n| parking             = yes\n| code                = 3029; 3030\n| opened              = {{Start date|2012|04|25|df=y}}\n| services            = {{s-rail|title=Sofia Metro}}\n{{s-line|system=Sofia Metro|line=Line 2|previous=Mladost 3|next=Druzhba}}\n| map_locator         = [[File:Map8 eng trans.png|300px]]\n}}\n{{Sofia Metro Blue line}}\n'''Inter Expo Center \u2013 Tsarigradsko shose Metro Station''' ({{lang-bg|\u041c\u0435\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0446\u0438\u044f \"\u0418\u043d\u0442\u0435\u0440 \u0415\u043a\u0441\u043f\u043e \u0426\u0435\u043d\u0442\u044a\u0440 - \u0426\u0430\u0440\u0438\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e \u0448\u043e\u0441\u0435\"}}) is a station on the [[Sofia Metro]] in [[Bulgaria]].  It started operation on April 25, 2012. Bulgaria's PM [[Boyko Borisov]] and [[President of the European Council|EU Council]] President [[Herman Van Rompuy]] inaugurated the new section of the Sofia Metro, which was funded with EU money.<ref>http://www.novinite.com/view_news.php?id=138809</ref> It is located on [[Tsarigradsko shose]].<ref>http://www.novinite.com/view_news.php?id=138409</ref>\n\n==Public Transportation==\n* [[Public buses in Sofia|City Bus service]]: 505\n* [[Public buses in Sofia|Suburban Bus service]]: 1, 3, 5, 6\n\n==Location==\n{{Empty section|date=October 2012}}\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nFile:\u041c\u0435\u0442\u0440\u043e-\u0426\u0430\u0440\u0438\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e.jpg\n</gallery>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commonscat-inline|Inter Expo Center - Tsarigradsko Shose (Sofia Metro)|IEC - Tsarigradsko shose}}\n* [http://www.metropolitan.bg/ Sofia Metropolitan]\n* [http://vijsofia.eu/bg/%D0%BF%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%B5%D0%BA%D1%82%D0%B8/%D0%B1%D1%83%D1%84%D0%B5%D1%80%D0%B5%D0%BD-%D0%BF%D0%B0%D1%80%D0%BA%D0%B8%D0%BD%D0%B3-%D0%BD%D0%B0-%D0%B1%D1%83%D0%BB-%D1%86%D0%B0%D1%80%D0%B8%D0%B3%D1%80%D0%B0%D0%B4%D1%81%D0%BA%D0%BE-%D1%88%D0%BE%D1%81%D0%B5-47/ Park and ride at the station]\n* [http://www.metropolitan.bg/en/gallery/view/23.html Sofia Metropolitan]\n\n{{Europe-metro-stub}}\n{{Bulgaria-transport-stub}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Inter Expo Center - Tsarigradsko shose Metro Station}}\n[[Category:Sofia Metro stations]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 2012]]\n[[Category:2012 establishments in Bulgaria]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox station\n| name                = [[File:Sofia Metro Logo.svg|27px|link=Sofia Metro]] IEC - Tsarigradsko shose\n| style               = Sofia Metro\n| image               = \u0426\u0430\u0440\u0438\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e-\u0432\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0431\u044e\u043b.jpg\n| coordinates         = {{coord|42|38|58.62|N|23|23|37.01|E|display=inline,title}}\n| owned               = [[Sofia#Administration|Sofia Municipality]]\n| platforms           = side\n| levels              = 3\n| tracks              = 2\n| structure           = sub-surface\n| parking             = yes\n| code                = 3029; 3030\n| opened              = {{Start date|2012|04|25|df=y}}\n| services            = {{s-rail|title=Sofia Metro}}\n{{s-line|system=Sofia Metro|line=Line 2|previous=Mladost 3|next=Druzhba}}\n| map_locator         = [[File:Map8 eng trans.png|300px]]\n}}\n{{Sofia Metro Blue line}}\n'''Inter Expo Center \u2013 Tsarigradsko shose Metro Station''' ({{lang-bg|\u041c\u0435\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0446\u0438\u044f \"\u0418\u043d\u0442\u0435\u0440 \u0415\u043a\u0441\u043f\u043e \u0426\u0435\u043d\u0442\u044a\u0440 - \u0426\u0430\u0440\u0438\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e \u0448\u043e\u0441\u0435\"}}) is a station on the [[Sofia Metro]] in [[Bulgaria]].  It started operation on April 25, 2012. Bulgaria's PM [[Boyko Borisov]] and [[President of the European Council|EU Council]] President [[Herman Van Rompuy]] inaugurated the new section of the Sofia Metro, which was funded with EU money.<ref>http://www.novinite.com/view_news.php?id=138809</ref> It is located on [[Tsarigradsko shose]].<ref>http://www.novinite.com/view_news.php?id=138409</ref>\n\n==Public Transportation==\n* [[Public buses in Sofia|City Bus service]]: 505\n* [[Public buses in Sofia|Suburban Bus service]]: 1, 3, 5, 6\n\n==Location==\n{{Empty section|date=October 2012}}\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nFile:\u041c\u0435\u0442\u0440\u043e-\u0426\u0430\u0440\u0438\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e.jpg\n</gallery>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commonscat-inline|Inter Expo Center - Tsarigradsko Shose (Sofia Metro)|IEC - Tsarigradsko shose}}\n* [http://www.metropolitan.bg/ Sofia Metropolitan]\n* [http://vijsofia.eu/bg/%D0%BF%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%B5%D0%BA%D1%82%D0%B8/%D0%B1%D1%83%D1%84%D0%B5%D1%80%D0%B5%D0%BD-%D0%BF%D0%B0%D1%80%D0%BA%D0%B8%D0%BD%D0%B3-%D0%BD%D0%B0-%D0%B1%D1%83%D0%BB-%D1%86%D0%B0%D1%80%D0%B8%D0%B3%D1%80%D0%B0%D0%B4%D1%81%D0%BA%D0%BE-%D1%88%D0%BE%D1%81%D0%B5-47/ Park and ride at the station]\n* [http://www.metropolitan.bg/en/gallery/view/23.html Sofia Metropolitan]\n\n{{Europe-metro-stub}}\n{{Bulgaria-transport-stub}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Inter Expo Center - Tsarigradsko shose Metro Station}}\n[[Category:Sofia Metro stations]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 2012]]\n[[Category:2012 establishments in Bulgaria]]\n", "name_user": "Ymblanter", "label": "safe", "